<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-087-190 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 077 001</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 5 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM andamp; Lotus work on 1-2-3 for RS/6000. (Lotus Development Corp.'sspreadsheet software)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbara E.; McMullen, John F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (Contracts)Lotus Development Corp. (Contracts).andO;Ticker:    LOTS; IBM.andO;Product:   Lotus 1-2-3 (Spreadsheet software) (Product enhancement)IBM RS/6000 (Workstation) (Computer programs).andO;Topic:     Cooperative AgreementProduct Development.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM andamp; LOTUS WORK ON 1-2-3 FOR RS/6000 08/05/91 WHITE PLAINS, NEW YORK,U.S.A., 1991 AUG 5 (NB) -- IBM and Lotus Development Corporation haveannounced an agreement under which that they will deliver Lotus 1-2-3spreadsheet application for the IBM RISC System/6000 family of workstationsand servers.andM;Under the agreement, IBM will provide equipment and support to Lotus, whichwill develop the software at its Dublin, Ireland facility.andP;  Although pricing,marketing, and availability information on Lotus 1- 2-3 for the RISCSystem/6000 will be announced at a later date, a Lotus source told Newsbytesthat availability is scheduled for 1992.andM;The new release will be based on Lotus 1-2-3 Release 3, which contains 3-Dspreadsheet capability with presentation-quality graphics, relationaldatabase support, and the 1-2-3 interface.andP;  Lotus spokesperson Lisa Landatold Newsbytes that the closest existing version to the new product is theversion for the Sun SPARC Workstation which is &quot;also based on the Release 3core technology.&quot;andM;Announcing the agreement, Bill Filip, IBM vice president and president,Advanced Workstations Division, said, &quot;Lotus 1-2-3 on the RISC System/6000will provide our customers a leading office application to help enhance theirbusiness productivity.andP;  IBM is pleased to add Lotus 1-2-3 to our growing listof more than 3,100 key RISC System/6000 software packages for both technicaland commercial users.&quot;andM;Bob Weiler, senior vice president of sales and marketing at Lotus, alsocommented on the agreement, saying, &quot;Bringing 1-2-3 to the RISC System/6000reinforces our goal to provide versions of 1-2-3 for all major platformsrequested by our customers.andP;  It's also further evidence of our strongrelationship with IBM, and our commitment to deliver networked,multi-platform suites of applications that help people work together.&quot;andM;When questioned by Newsbytes concerning the choice of Dublin for thedevelopment, Lotus' Landa explained, &quot;Dublin is the location from which weprovide the development support for our international versions and there is astrong base of Unix knowledge at that location.andP;  As you know, we alwaysattempt to release our international versions very close to our US releasesand the Dublin staff has great experience in building on the Release coretechnology.&quot;andM;(Barbara E. McMullen andamp; John F. McMullen/Press Contacts: Judy Radlinsky, IBM,914-642-4634; Lisa Landa of Lotus, 617-693- 1263/19910805)</TEXT></DOC>